{
  "texts": [
    "Weng et al. (2021) propose to leverage the hierarchical structure of objects within images to perform weaklysupervised long-tail instance segmentation.",
    "To capture this hierarchical structure, Weng et al. (2021) learn hyperbolic representations which are supervised with several hyperbolic self-supervised losses.",
    "Instance segmentation is done in three stages: first, mask proposals are generated using a pre-trained mask proposal network.",
    "Mask proposals consists of bounding boxes {B i } k i=1 and masks {M i } k i=1.",
    "Define x full i to be the original image cropped to bounding box B i, x bg i to be the cropped image with the object masked out using mask 1-M i, and x fg i to be the same cropped image with the background masked out using mask M i."
  ]
}